About.Features.Title: Features
About.Features.InfoHub.Description: No about-service present, use R&D infohub for component versions
About.3rdPartySoftwareIntro: The following list shows all third-party software and licenses used in Qlik Sense. All are vital parts of Qlik Sense.
Template.preview.description.barchart: Compare multiple values, with one bar for each dimension value. Use grouped bars to compare items of the same category. Use stacked bars to compare the totals of items across categories.
Template.preview.description.combochart: Compare two sets of measure values using different scales, for example, sum and margin. Combine bars and lines to show the relationship.
Template.preview.description.container: The container object can hold multiple objects of any type, except a second container. In a container you can toggle between several objects using the same sheet area.
Template.preview.description.linechart: Display trends over time, for example, sales per month. Add another dimension, Year, to compare the trend for different years. Use stacked area to show totals.
Template.preview.description.filterpane: Display dimension values to enable the precise selection of a data set.
Template.preview.description.piechart: Display relation between values but also between a single value and the total. Use with up to 10 dimension values.
Template.preview.description.scatterplot: Display the relationship between two measures, one on each axis, for example, sales and cost. Each point is a dimension value. A third measure can be used and reflected in the point size.
Template.preview.description.table: Display several measure values for each dimension value. Show the totals for each measure. Sort columns and rows alphabetically or numerically. Change sorting during analysis.
Template.preview.description.text-image: Display text, images, links, and measures. Format and color the text, add background images, and highlight key measure values.
Template.preview.description.map: Display point and area data. Plot sales in a region and use the point size to reflect the measure value. Add a background map to point data.
